DORCHESTER COUNTY SURVEYOR'S OFFICE
PROPERTY SURVEY — PLAT NO. 1938-0447

Property: Pratt, Earl J.
Location: Shorter's Wharf Road, Election District 4
Acreage: 187 acres
Surveyed: 14 September 1938

BOUNDARY: Beginning at the iron pipe at Shorter's Wharf Rd and the county road, thence S 22° E along county road 1,287 ft to Tolson line, thence N 68° E along Tolson 2,440 ft to mean high water mark of the Little Blackwater, thence northerly along said mark approx. 1,940 ft, thence S 68° W approx. 2,180 ft to beginning.

NOTES:
— Eastern boundary follows mean high water mark, subject to variation
— USGS station BW-14 at survey marker No. 7 (installed 1928)

{LATER ANNOTATIONS — undated, hand unknown:}
{One small circle drawn on eastern boundary at marker 7.}
{Inside the circle: '1962'}
{Below: 'BW-14. It always starts here.'}

{Three additional circles at markers 1, 3, 5 — dated '1914,' '1931,' '1947' respectively. No annotations on these.}

{Four circles total. Four active cycles. The intervals are shrinking.}
